data.name: GoToStateActionTargetHasNoStateGroups
data.value: Target {0} does not define any VisualStateGroups.
data.comment: {0} is an element name and could be an empty string

data.name: UnsupportedRemoveTargetExceptionMessage
data.value: The target of the RemoveElementAction is not supported.

data.name: ChangePropertyActionCannotFindPropertyNameExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot find a property named "{0}" on type "{1}".
data.comment: {0} is the PropertyName property value specified by the user {1} is the Type we are trying to find a property on

data.name: ChangePropertyActionCannotSetValueExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot assign value of type "{0}" to property "{1}" of type "{2}". The "{1}" property can be assigned only values of type "{2}".
data.comment: {0} is the type name of the illegal value, or "null" if value is null {1} is the name of the property {2} is the type of the property

data.name: ChangePropertyActionPropertyIsReadOnlyExceptionMessage
data.value: Property "{0}" defined by type "{1}" does not expose a set method and therefore cannot be modified.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the property {1} is the name of the type that defines the property

data.name: ChangePropertyActionCannotIncrementAnimatedPropertyChangeExceptionMessage
data.value: The Increment property cannot be set to True if the Duration property is set.
data.comment: This message is shown if a user attempts to animate and increment a property change.

data.name: ChangePropertyActionCannotAnimateTargetTypeExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot animate a property change on a type '{0}' Target. Property changes can only be animated on types derived from DependencyObject.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the type the user tried to target. This message is shown if a user attempts to animate a property on a non-DependencyObject type.

data.name: ChangePropertyActionCannotIncrementWriteOnlyPropertyExceptionMessage
data.value: The '{0}' property cannot be incremented because its value cannot be read.
data.comment: {0} is the name of write-only property This message is shown if a user attempts to increment a write-only property.

data.name: ChangePropertyActionAmbiguousAdditionOperationExceptionMessage
data.value: More than one potential addition operator was found on type '{0}'.
data.comment: {0} is the type on which multiple usable op_Addition overloads were found. Shown when attempting to increment using an type with more than one applicable op_Addition method defined.

data.name: InvalidLeftOperand
data.value: LeftOperand of type "{0}" cannot be used with operator "{1}".
data.comment: Exception thrown by ConditionalExpression. {0} represent an english type, {1} represent an english operator 'greaterthan'. Both are non localizable

data.name: InvalidOperands
data.value: LeftOperand of type "{1}" and RightOperand of type "{0}" cannot be used with operator "{2}".
data.comment: Exception thrown by ConditionalExpression. {0}and {1} represent an english type, {2} represent an english operator 'greaterthan'. Both are non localizable

data.name: InvalidRightOperand
data.value: RightOperand of type "{0}" cannot be used with operator "{1}".
data.comment: Exception thrown by ConditionalExpression. {0} represents an english type, {1} represent an english operator 'greaterthan'. Both are non localizable

data.name: CallMethodActionValidMethodNotFoundExceptionMessage
data.value: Could not find method named '{0}' on object of type '{1}' that matches the expected signature.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the method that could not be found {1} is the name of the type that was searched for the method

data.name: DataStateBehaviorStateNameNotFoundExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot find state named '{0}' on type '{1}'. Ensure that the state exists and that it can be accessed from this context.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the state that could not be found {1} is the name of the type that was searched for the state, or null if that type was null

data.name: CannotHostBehaviorCollectionMultipleTimesExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot set the same BehaviorCollection on multiple objects.

data.name: CannotHostBehaviorMultipleTimesExceptionMessage
data.value: An instance of a Behavior cannot be attached to more than one object at a time.

data.name: CannotHostTriggerActionMultipleTimesExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot host an instance of a TriggerAction in multiple TriggerCollections simultaneously. Remove it from one TriggerCollection before adding it to another.

data.name: CannotHostTriggerCollectionMultipleTimesExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot set the same TriggerCollection on multiple objects.

data.name: CannotHostTriggerMultipleTimesExceptionMessage
data.value: An instance of a trigger cannot be attached to more than one object at a time.

data.name: CommandDoesNotExistOnBehaviorWarningMessage
data.value: The command "{0}" does not exist or is not publicly exposed on {1}.
data.comment: {0} is the non-existant command name the user specified. {1} is the type name of the Behavior the command could not be found on.

data.name: DefaultTriggerAttributeInvalidTriggerTypeSpecifiedExceptionMessage
data.value: "{0}" is not a valid type for the TriggerType parameter. Make sure "{0}" derives from TriggerBase.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the type the user specified

data.name: DuplicateItemInCollectionExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot add the same instance of "{0}" to a "{1}" more than once.
data.comment: {0} is the name of the type being added to the collection. {1} is the type name of the collection

data.name: EventTriggerBaseInvalidEventExceptionMessage
data.value: The event "{0}" on type "{1}" has an incompatible signature. Make sure the event is public and satisfies the EventHandler delegate.
data.comment: {0} is the EventName property value specified by the user. {1} is the Type we are trying to find an event on

data.name: EventTriggerCannotFindEventNameExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot find an event named "{0}" on type "{1}".
data.comment: {0} is the EventName property value specified by the user. {1} is the Type we are trying to find an event on

data.name: RetargetedTypeConstraintViolatedExceptionMessage
data.value: An object of type "{0}" cannot have a {3} property of type "{1}". Instances of type "{0}" can have only a {3} property of type "{2}".
data.comment: {0} is the type name of the constrained type. {1} is the type name of the object to which the constrained type's property cannot be set. {2} is the type name of the type to which instances of the constrained type's property can be set. {3} is either "Source" or "Target", depending on the constrained type's property name

data.name: TypeConstraintViolatedExceptionMessage
data.value: Cannot attach type "{0}" to type "{1}". Instances of type "{0}" can only be attached to objects of type "{2}".
data.comment: {0} is the type name of the constrained type. {1} is the type name of the object to which the constrainted type cannot be attached. {2} is the type name of the constraint type

data.name: UnableToResolveTargetNameWarningMessage
data.value: Unable to resolve TargetName "{0}".
data.comment: {0} is the user-specified TargetName that could not be resolved.
